cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it introduces a toolkit for production-level machine learning. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as machine learning is often used in computer vision applications. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. The paper also mentions optimization algorithms, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the use of classifiers and regressors suggests it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
